41#define MXSERV 20
42#define MXNAME (DNS_NAME_MAXTEXT+1)
43#define MXRD 32
44/*% Buffer Size */
45#define BUFSIZE 512
46#define COMMSIZE 0xffff
47#ifndef RESOLV_CONF
48/*% location of resolve.conf */
49#define RESOLV_CONF "/etc/resolv.conf"
50#endif
51/*% output buffer */
52#define OUTPUTBUF 32767
53/*% Max RR Limit */
54#define MAXRRLIMIT 0xffffffff
55#define MAXTIMEOUT 0xffff
56/*% Max number of tries */
57#define MAXTRIES 0xffffffff
58/*% Max number of dots */
59#define MAXNDOTS 0xffff
60/*% Max number of ports */
61#define MAXPORT 0xffff
62/*% Max serial number */
63#define MAXSERIAL 0xffffffff
64
65/*% Default TCP Timeout */
66#define TCP_TIMEOUT 10
67/*% Default UDP Timeout */
68#define UDP_TIMEOUT 5
69
70#define SERVER_TIMEOUT 1
71
72#define LOOKUP_LIMIT 64
73/*%
74 * Lookup_limit is just a limiter, keeping too many lookups from being
75 * created. It's job is mainly to prevent the program from running away
76 * in a tight loop of constant lookups. It's value is arbitrary.
77 */

89#define DIG_VALID_QUERY(x) ISC_MAGIC_VALID((x), DIG_QUERY_MAGIC)

92/*% The dig_lookup structure */
93struct dig_lookup {
94 bool
95 pending, /*%< Pending a successful answer */
96 waiting_connect,
97 doing_xfr,
98 ns_search_only, /*%< dig +nssearch, host -C */
99 identify, /*%< Append an "on server <foo>" message */
100 identify_previous_line, /*% Prepend a "Nameserver <foo>:"
101 message, with newline and tab */
102 ignore,
103 recurse,
104 aaonly,
105 adflag,
106 cdflag,
107 raflag,
108 tcflag,
109 zflag,
110 trace, /*% dig +trace */
111 trace_root, /*% initial query for either +trace or +nssearch */
112 tcp_mode,
113 tcp_mode_set,
114 comments,
115 stats,
116 section_question,
117 section_answer,
118 section_authority,
119 section_additional,
120 servfail_stops,
121 new_search,
122 need_search,
123 done_as_is,
124 besteffort,
125 dnssec,
126 expire,
127 sendcookie,
128 seenbadcookie,
129 badcookie,
130 nsid, /*% Name Server ID (RFC 5001) */
131 tcp_keepalive,
132 header_only,
133 ednsneg,
134 mapped,
135 print_unknown_format,
136 multiline,
137 nottl,
138 noclass,
139 onesoa,
140 use_usec,
141 nocrypto,
142 ttlunits,
143 idnin,
144 idnout,
145 qr;
146 char textname[MXNAME]; /*% Name we're going to be looking up */
147 char cmdline[MXNAME];
148 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype;
149 dns_rdatatype_t qrdtype;
150 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass;
151 bool rdtypeset;
152 bool rdclassset;
153 char name_space[BUFSIZE];
154 char oname_space[BUFSIZE];
155 isc_buffer_t namebuf;
156 isc_buffer_t onamebuf;
157 isc_buffer_t renderbuf;
158 char *sendspace;
159 dns_name_t *name;
160 isc_interval_t interval;
161 dns_message_t *sendmsg;
162 dns_name_t *oname;
163 ISC_LINK(dig_lookup_t) link;
164 ISC_LIST(dig_query_t) q;
165 ISC_LIST(dig_query_t) connecting;
166 dig_query_t *current_query;
167 dig_serverlist_t my_server_list;
168 dig_searchlist_t *origin;
169 dig_query_t *xfr_q;
170 uint32_t retries;
171 int nsfound;
172 uint16_t udpsize;
173 int16_t edns;
174 int16_t padding;
175 uint32_t ixfr_serial;
176 isc_buffer_t rdatabuf;
177 char rdatastore[MXNAME];
178 dst_context_t *tsigctx;
179 isc_buffer_t *querysig;
180 uint32_t msgcounter;
181 dns_fixedname_t fdomain;
182 isc_sockaddr_t *ecs_addr;
183 char *cookie;
184 dns_ednsopt_t *ednsopts;
185 unsigned int ednsoptscnt;
186 isc_dscp_t dscp;
187 unsigned int ednsflags;
188 dns_opcode_t opcode;
189 int rrcomments;
190 unsigned int eoferr;
191};
192
193/*% The dig_query structure */
194struct dig_query {
195 unsigned int magic;
196 dig_lookup_t *lookup;
197 bool waiting_connect,
198 pending_free,
199 waiting_senddone,
200 first_pass,
201 first_soa_rcvd,
202 second_rr_rcvd,
203 first_repeat_rcvd,
204 recv_made,
205 warn_id,
206 timedout;
207 uint32_t first_rr_serial;
208 uint32_t second_rr_serial;
209 uint32_t msg_count;
210 uint32_t rr_count;
211 bool ixfr_axfr;
212 char *servname;
213 char *userarg;
214 isc_buffer_t recvbuf,
215 lengthbuf,
216 tmpsendbuf,
217 sendbuf;
218 char *recvspace, *tmpsendspace,
219 lengthspace[4];
220 isc_socket_t *sock;
221 ISC_LINK(dig_query_t) link;
222 ISC_LINK(dig_query_t) clink;
223 isc_sockaddr_t sockaddr;
224 isc_time_t time_sent;
225 isc_time_t time_recv;
226 uint64_t byte_count;
227 isc_timer_t *timer;
228};

231 char servername[MXNAME];
232 char userarg[MXNAME];
233 ISC_LINK(dig_server_t) link;
234};
